    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Another option is to use <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/text/DecimalFormat.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">DecimalFormat</a> to format your numeric String. Here is one other way to do the job without having to use String.format if you are stuck in the pre 1.5 world:</p>\n\n<pre><code>static String intToString(int num, int digits) {\n    assert digits &gt; 0 : \"Invalid number of digits\";\n\n    // create variable length array of zeros\n    char[] zeros = new char[digits];\n    Arrays.fill(zeros, '0');\n    // format number as String\n    DecimalFormat df = new DecimalFormat(String.valueOf(zeros));\n\n    return df.format(num);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
